WEBVTT

00:00.459 --> 00:01.995
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

00:05.172 --> 00:07.038
Well... (SIGHS)
spring has sprung.

00:07.341 --> 00:09.173
The food truck business
is about to boom,

00:09.468 --> 00:11.675
which means once again | have
to contend with my archenemy,

00:11.970 --> 00:12.755
the Brazilian.

00:15.307 --> 00:16.341
What's wrong
with you guys?

00:16.642 --> 00:17.723
Normally, you'd
razz me pretty hard

00:18.018 --> 00:18.928
when I say things like
"Spring has sprung.”

00:19.228 --> 00:20.434
Or when I walk into
a room.

00:22.481 --> 00:23.687
"Five way jinx."
Really?

00:25.651 --> 00:27.141
"Yes, really!”

00:27.444 --> 00:28.775
All right, fine. Max,
Penny, Brad, Jane, Alex.

00:29.071 --> 00:29.731
(MAX, PENNY, AND BRAD
SHOUT AT ONCE) Unjinxed.

00:30.030 --> 00:32.522
(GASPS)

00:32.824 --> 00:33.985
(LAUGHS) You don't have to
hold your breath when you're jinxed.

00:34.284 --> 00:35.115
| play prison rules.

00:35.410 --> 00:36.320
They play jinx in prison?

00:36.620 --> 00:38.577
Guys, back to my thing!
The Brazilian.

00:38.872 --> 00:39.737
Oh, you mean that guy with
the awesome steak truck...

00:40.040 --> 00:41.656
Rio De Ja-tasty?

00:41.959 --> 00:44.200
Oh, I love that guy. He has
the best churrascherascia.

00:44.503 --> 00:45.493
It's... (IMITATES BRAZILIAN
ACCENT) Churrascherascia.

00:45.796 --> 00:46.831
Ugh.
Gross.

00:47.130 --> 00:48.541
Anyway,
the guy's a real jerk.

00:48.840 --> 00:50.922
He's always sabotaging me,
trying to steal my business.

00:51.218 --> 00:52.834
Just fight back
like you did in high school

00:53.136 --> 00:54.251
when those kids stole
your can of mousse.

00:54.555 --> 00:56.137
Oh, wait.
You didn't fight back.

00:56.431 --> 00:57.512
You just hid
in the yearbook office

00:57.808 --> 00:59.139
and complained that
your hair wasn't hard enough.

00:59.434 --> 01:00.890
Penny,
this dude is hard-core.

01:01.186 --> 01:02.551
One time, he plugged an
exhaust vent in my truck

01:02.854 --> 01:04.218
with human manure.

01:04.522 --> 01:06.685
And he's always calling in
fake to-go orders.

01:06.984 --> 01:08.474
You didn't think it was weird
that Dean Cain asked you

01:08.777 --> 01:10.734
to cater an 1,100
person bachelor party?

01:11.029 --> 01:12.144
No, Jane, | didn't
think it was weird

01:12.447 --> 01:14.688
because it was
Dean freakin' Cain.

01:14.992 --> 01:16.153
Oh.
The point is,

01:16.451 --> 01:18.818
| gotta be a man
and stand up for myself...

01:19.121 --> 01:20.828
On my own, with
you guys behind me...

01:21.123 --> 01:22.659
Brad, maybe you more
towards the front,

01:22.958 --> 01:24.995
perhaps wearing
some Raiders gear?

01:25.294 --> 01:27.831
Well, us gals can't help
"cause we're too busy

01:28.130 --> 01:30.792
doing some last-minute details
for the old wedding.

01:31.091 --> 01:33.628
Yep. I'm officially
in the wedding red zone.

01:33.927 --> 01:35.042
See, I put that in sports terms
SO you guys could understand.

01:36.221 --> 01:38.007
We're in
the eighth quarter, boys,

01:38.307 --> 01:40.639
about to put some sports
points up on the score yard.

01:40.934 --> 01:43.175
Oops. I think
(SLURRING) I fumbled the ball.

01:43.478 --> 01:45.435
(WHISTLES) Turn under.

01:45.731 --> 01:48.393
Well, Brad, Max?
| don't know.

01:48.692 --> 01:51.354
